{
  "rule": "lax_friedrichs_flux",
  "applicable": false,
  "skip_reason": "lax_friedrichs_flux is the dissipative first-order LF numerical flux F_{i+1/2} = max(c,0)·q_i + min(c,0)·q_{i+1}, parameterised by a face-staggered Courant binding `$c`. Two issues block the §7 verify_mms_convergence harness today: (1) the rule output is at the face stagger (i+1/2), not cell-centred — the harness's smooth-MMS sweep is wired for cell-centred outputs; (2) the per-face Courant binding `$c` is not yet supported by the harness's binding contract (today only scalar bindings like `dx`, `R`, `cos_lat` are bound at sweep time — face fields are the same gap that holds back centered_2nd_uniform_latlon's `cos_lat` per dsc-7jc, scoped here as the LF-specific instance of dsc-cuj's stagger-aware binding follow-up). When applied as part of a full transport scheme (LF flux + FV divergence + forward Euler on uniform Cartesian linear advection), the scheme is theoretically O(h) in L_inf — a follow-up Layer-B′ MMS-transport fixture (mirroring the limiter `tvd_check.esm`) is the right shape, not a bare reconstruction-style sweep. Hand-pinned single-face flux values live inline in test/test_lax_friedrichs_flux_rule.jl (the walker-discoverable `canonical/` directory is intentionally omitted because ESS's `discretize` does not yet support op=\"flux\" with per-face bindings)."
}
